href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-sora-new-video-generator-model-ai-sam-altman-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%20Sora%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESora%20can%20generate%20videos%20up%20to%20a%20minute%20long%20that%20can%20consist%20of%20%26quot%3Bcomplex%20scenes%20with%20multiple%20characters%2C%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fsora%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20was%20unveiled.%20Demos%20of%20the%20Sora-generated%20videos%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FOpenAI%2Fstatus%2F1758192957386342435%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewent%20viral%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February%20and%20seemed%20to%20impress%20many%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20its%20own%20text-to-video%20generator%2C%20Lumiere%2C%20which%20it%20revealed%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2401.12945%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January.%20It%20can%20generate%20five-second%20clips%20with%20a%20text%20prompt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fsundarpichai%2Fstatus%2F1758145921131630989%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20released%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20experimental%20AI%20model%20Gemini%201.5%2C%20said%20in%20the%20research%20paper%20it's%20crucial%20to%20create%20tools%20that%20can%20detect%20%26quot%3Bbiases%20and%20malicious%20use%20cases%26quot%3B%20to%20ensure%20it's%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Brisk%20of%20misuse%20for%20creating%20fake%20or%20harmful%20content%26quot%3B%20with%20Lumiere%2C%20and%20it%20faced%20such%20an%20issue%20with%20Gemini's%20image%20generator%20in%20February.%20Google%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google%2Fproducts%2Fgemini%2Fgemini-image-generation-issue%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaused%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20rollout%20of%20its%20image%20generator%20after%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-gemini-ai-pause-image-generation-people-woke-complaints-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproduced%20images%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20people%20of%20color%20in%20historically%20inaccurate%20contexts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHassabis'%20take%20on%20Lumiere%20compared%20with%20Sora%20comes%20as%20Big%20Tech%20firms%20continue%20in%20an%20AI%20race%20with%20rival%20products.%20But%20securing%20a%20victory%20hinges%20on%20getting%20a%20sizable%20amount%20of%20data%20to%20feed%20their%20systems%20and%20push%20the%20technology%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20chief%20technology%20officer%2C%20Mira%20Murati%2C%20told%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DmAUpxN-EIgU%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcould-openai-be-violating-youtubes-terms-of-service-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edidn't%20know%20if%20Sora%20had%20been%20trained%20on%20YouTube%3C%2Fa%3E%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20CEO%20Neal%20Mohan%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-04-04%2Fyoutube-says-openai-training-sora-with-its-videos-would-break-the-rules%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Bloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20he%20had%20no%20knowledge%20of%20whether%20OpenAI%20was%20using%20YouTube%20content%20to%20train%20its%20video%20generator.%20He%20added%20that%20doing%20so%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bclear%20violation%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20platform's%20terms%20of%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F04%2F06%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-giants-harvest-data-artificial-intelligence.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20that%20OpenAI%20used%20YouTube%20videos%20to%20help%20improve%20its%20speech%