0as%20the%20impacts%20of%20warming%20temperatures%2C%20higher%20sea%20levels%2C%20and%20more%20extreme%20storms%20worsen%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20as%20millennials%2C%20who%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-buying-homes-stress-about-climate-risk-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20concerned%20about%20climate%20risks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20grow%20as%20a%20share%20of%20homebuyers.%20And%20Miami%20is%20far%20from%20alone%20%E2%80%94%20coastal%20flooding%2C%20extreme%20heat%2C%20and%20other%20climate%20impacts%20are%20affecting%20cities%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20many%20US%20cities%2C%20lower-come%20and%20predominantly%20Black%20neighborhoods%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2022%2F07%2Fblack-communities-us-flood-risk-climate%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBlack%2520communities%2520in%2520the%2520United%2Cstreet%2520basis%2520across%2520the%2520US.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealready%20exist%20in%20areas%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20less%20tree%20cover%2C%20higher%20temperatures%2C%20and%20a%20greater%20risk%20of%20flooding.%20Black%20residents%20of%20Southeastern%20states%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20live%20in%20places%20heavily%20impacted%20by%20excessive%20heat%2C%20flooding%2C%20and%20hurricanes%2C%20an%20analysis%20by%20consultants%20at%20McKinsey%C2%A0%26amp%3B%20Company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F12%2F01%2Fus%2Fblack-communities-greater-climate-risk-reaj%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%20in%20late%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Miami%20could%20have%20around%2080%2C000%20properties%20flooding%20by%20mid-century%2C%20a%20multibillion-dollar%20risk%2C%20due%20to%20the%20combination%20of%20sinking%20land%20and%20rising%20seas%2C%20researchers%20say.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660eb94e16bde8d4ead59f5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5