o%20collect%20Social%20Security%2C%20on%20top%20of%20drawing%20from%20the%20nest%20egg%20you've%20built%20up%20over%20your%20career.%20Free%20from%20the%20shackles%20of%20a%209-to-5%2C%20you%20can%20finally%20do%20all%20the%20things%20you've%20been%20waiting%20for%3A%20spend%20time%20with%20your%20grandkids%2C%20travel%20across%20the%20country%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fsimple-strategy-to-save-enough-for-retirement-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20an%20RV%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscary-cruise-ship-facts-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehop%20on%20a%20cruise%20ship%20(if%20you%20dare)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20this%20story%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-today-retirement-crisis-america-social-security-boomers-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20feels%20like%20a%20fairy%20tale%3C%2Fa%3E%20that's%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20a%20golden%20sunset%20to%20look%20forward%20to%2C%20retirement%20has%20become%20anxiety-inducing%20for%20many%20people%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20just%20because%20of%20the%20get-old-and-die%20thing%20that%20comes%20at%20the%20end.%20Millions%20of%20Americans%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fsigns-you-have-enough-saved-for-retirement-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworried%20they%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20retire%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20way%20they'd%20like%2C%20and%20they're%20afraid%20they'll%20run%20out%20of%20money%20once%20they%20stop%20working.%20In%20a%20Gallup%20poll%20last%20year%2C%2043%25%20of%20non-retirees%20said%20they%20thought%20they'd%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20live%20comfortably%20once%20they're%20ready%20to%20hang%20up%20their%20proverbial%20aprons%2C%20and%2071%25%20said%20they%20were%20at%20least%20moderately%20worried%20about%20being%20able%20to%20pay%20for%20their%20retirement.%20(It%20is%20worth%20noting%20that%20current%20retirees%2C%20as%20in%20boomers%2C%20feel%20a%20lot%20better%20about%20the%20whole%20deal.)%20In%20a%20recent%20CNBC%20survey%2C%20over%20half%20of%20respondents%20in%20the%20US%20said%20they%20thought%20they%20were%20behind%20on%20saving%20and%20planning%20for%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pessimism%20is%20understandable%3A%20People%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fretirement%2Fretirement-savings-needed-increased-2024-9f7c01e0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimate%20they%20need%20about%20%241.5%20million%20to%20live%20as%20they%20want%20to%20in%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20only%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20savers%20actually%20have%20that%20amount%20stashed%20away.%20Teresa%20Ghilarducci%2C%20a%20labor%20economist%20at%20The%20New%20School%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BWork%2C%20Retire%2C%20Repeat%3A%20The%20Uncertainty%20of%20Retirement%20in%20the%20New%20Economy%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20me%20that%20given%20these%20expectations%2C%20the%20anxiety%20is%20well%20founded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20irrational%20about%20being%20nervous%20that%20you%20won't%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20live%20on%20to%20last%20your%20whole%20life%2C%20because%20most%20people%20do%20not%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20last%20their%20whole%20life%20and%20maintain%20their%20standard%20of%20living%20in%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fgeneration-x-behind-retirement-savings-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburden%20of%20saving%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20anxiety%20that%20comes%20with%20it%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20fairly%20new%20phenomenon.%20Until%20the%201980s%2C%20American%20workers%20generally%20received%20money%20in%20retirement%20via%20defined-benefit%20plans%2C%20such%20as%20pensions%2C%20where%20their%20employers%20paid%20them%20a%20set%20amount%20depending%20on%20how%20long%20they'd%20worked%20at%20the%20company%20and%20how%20much%20money%20they'd%20made.%20Over%20the%20past%2040%20years%2C%20however%2C%20the%20approach%20has%20changed.%20Workers%20have%20shifted%20to%20defined-contribution%20plans%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-the-401k-isnt-working-2016-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)s%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20IRAs%2C%20where%20they%20(and%2C%20perhaps%2C%20their%20employers)%20kick%20into%20a%20fund%20that's%20usually%20invested%20to%20help%20them%20save%20up%20for%20older%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20system%20puts%20the%20impetus%20on%20individual%20employees%20to%20decide%20how%20much%20to%20save%20and%20how%20to%20invest%20it.%20In%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkey-takeaways-blackrock-ceo-larry-finks-letter-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20letter%20to%20investors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20BlackRock%20CEO%20Larry%20Fink%20addressed%20the%20conundrum.%20While%20much%20of%20society%20is%20focused%20on%20helping%20people%20live%20longer%20lives%2C%20he%20said%2C%20there's%20not%20much%20focus%20on%20helping%20them%20afford%20those%20longer%20lives.%20The%20move%20from%20pensions%20to%20401(k)s%20for%20millions%20of%20workers%20represents%20an%20%26quot%3Bimpossible%20math%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20because%20it's%20so%20hard%20for%20people%20to%20decipher%20how%20much%20money%20they'll%20need%20and%20how%20fast%20they'll%20spend%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPut%20simply%2C%26quot%3B%20Fink%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20shift%20from%20defined%20benefit%20to%20defined%20contribution%20has%20been%2C%20for%20most%20people%2C%20a%20shift%20from%20financial%20certainty%20to%20financial%20uncertainty.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20system%20also%20allows%20people%20to%20dip%20into%20their%20retirement%20piles%20if%20need%20be%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20be%20both%20a%20blessing%20and%20a%20curse.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20that%20money%20can%20act%20as%20a%20lifesaver%20in%20a%20preretirement%20emergency.%20On%20the%20other%2C%20dipping%20into%20it%20may%20mean%20running%20out%20of%20money%20down%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20probably%20not%20a%20great%20idea%20to%20let%20people%20draw%20on%20their%20retirement%20assets%20before%20they%20reach%20retirement%20age%2C%20but%20if%20you%20don't%20let%20people%20do%20that%2C%20they're%20not%20as%20likely%20to%20contribute%20to%20a%20401(k)%20plan%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Norman%20Stein%2C%20a%20professor%20emeritus%20of%20law%20at%20Drexel%20University's%20Thomas%20R.%20Kline%20School%20of%20Law.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20basically%20a%20savings%20system%20with%20a%20reasonably%20strong%20orientation%20toward%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Woods%2C%20a%20financial%20advisor%20who%20founded%20Silvis%20Financial%2C%20based%20in%20Charlotte%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20told%20me%20that%20all%20this%20uncertainty%20is%20often%20the%20reason%20clients%20wind%20up%20in%20his%20office.%20They're%20not%20only%20worried%20about%20having%20enough%20money%20to%20support%20themselves%20in%20retirement%20but%20concerned%20about%20all%20the%20other%20financial%20curveballs%20life%20may%20throw%20at%20them%20in%20their%20golden%20years%3A%20what%20their%20medical%20costs%20might%20be%2C%20whether%20their%20children%20might%20need%20help%2C%20whether%20they%20might%20get%20divorced%2C%20where%20they%20want%20to%20live.%20The%20overarching%20theme%20is%20having%20enough%20money%20to%20retire%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20then%20subsets%20of%20that%20that%20are%20unique%20to%20families%20based%20on%20health%2C%20family%2C%20even%20location%20and%20things%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20level%20of%20doomerism%20around%20how%20the%20federal%20government%20will%20financially%20support%20its%20citizens%20in%20the%20future%20as%20they%20reach%20old%20age.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-social-security-run-out-pay-full-benefits-plan-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%20trust%20fund%20is%20expected%20to%20run%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20money%20in%20about%20a%20decade%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-benefits-republicans-raise-age-retirement-cuts-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERepublicans%20often%20talk%20about%20making%20changes%20and%20cuts%20to%20the%20program%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20GOP%20sometimes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-republicans-social-security-and-medicare-medicaid-mccarthy-biden-debt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emakes%20noise%20about%20scaling%20back%20Medicare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20government-administered%20health-insurance%20program%2C%20too.%20Regardless%20of%20one's%20political%20stripes%2C%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicare%20are%20enormous%20government%20expenses%2C%20and%20given%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fmoney%2F2023%2F12%2F18%2F24001984%2Fus-budget-deficit-2023-debt-tax-revenue-interest-rates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econcerns%20about%20the%20country's%20debt%20and%20deficit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20hard%20not%20to%20wonder%20whether%20those%20programs%20will%20remain%20untouched.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20likely%20that%20Social%20Security%20will%20just%20dry%20up%20%E2%80%94%20Congress%20could%20increase%20the%20retirement%20age%20or%20up%20the%20funding%20for%20the%20program.%20But%20it's%20impossible%20to%20know%20whether%20it%20will%20be%20intact%20by%20the%20time%20many%20young%20people%20reach%20retirement.%20Of%20course%2C%20it%20could%2C%20at%20least%20in%20theory%2C%20get%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20debate%20shouldn't%20be%20on%20cutting%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20Stein%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20should%20be%20on%20how%20we%20preserve%20and%20improve%20the%20current%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20the%20financials%20of%20retirement%20that%20are%20scary.%20There's%20a%20significant%20emotional%20weight%20to%20it%2C%20too.%20Riley%20Moynes%2C%20a%20retired%20educator%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Four%20Phases%20of%20Retirement%3A%20What%20to%20Expect%20When%20You're%20Retiring%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20that%20for%20many%20people%2C%20the%20first%20year%20or%20so%20of%20retiring%20is%20exciting.%20They're%20free%20from%20work%3B%20they%20have%20time%20to%20relax%20and%20get%20moving%20on%20plans.%20But%20that%20soon%20shifts.%20People%20begin%20to%20feel%20lost.%20They%20need%20to%20make%20a%20conscious%20effort%20to%20reinvent%20themselves%20and%20find%20a%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20of%20retirement%20planning%20has%20been%20focused%20on%20investments.%20It's%20been%20focused%20on%20wills%2C%20powers%20of%20attorney%2C%20and%20all%20of%20that%20kind%20of%20stuff%20%E2%80%94%20critically%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20the%20psychological%20changes%20and%20challenges%20that%20people%20are%20going%20to%20experience%2C%20absolutely%2C%20are%20virtually%20overlooked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20so%20many%20unknowns%20that%20come%20with%20retirement%3A%20how%20one%20will%20feel%20emotionally%2C%20how%20they'll%20feel%20physically.%20Money%20isn't%20the%20be-all%20and%20end-all%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20big%20part%20of%20it.%20The%20unknown%20is%20unnerving%20in%20any%20circumstance%2C%20especially%20one%20where%20the%20end%20game%20is%20being%20able%20to%20pay%20for%20your%20life%20until%20you%20die%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20if%20you're%20lucky%2C%20leave%20some%20money%20behind%20for%20your%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20started%20reporting%20this%20story%2C%20I%20didn't%20realize%20just%20how%20freaked%20out%20I%20was%20by%20retirement.%20But%20after%20losing%20some%20sleep%20over%20my%20financial%20future%2C%20I%20asked%20the%20experts%20for%20advice%20on%20what%20to%20do%20to%20assuage%20my%20newfound%20(or%20at%20least%20newly%20examined)%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGhilarducci%2C%20the%20labor%20economist%2C%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20your%20spending%20and%20saving.%20If%20you're%20starting%20early%2C%20in%20your%2020s%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20stash%20away%20as%20much%20of%20your%20income%20as%20you%20do%20if%20you're%20starting%20later.%20Invest%20the%20money%2C%20and%20make%20sure%20the%20person%20or%20entity%20you're%20entrusting%20to%20oversee%20that%20investment%20is%20looking%20out%20for%20you.%20Be%20careful%20of%20conflicted%20and%20bad%20advice.%20And%20then%20there's%20the%20democracy%20aspect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20a%20voter%2C%20and%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20you%20need%20to%20know%20is%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicare%20are%20the%20most%20important%20sources%20of%20income%20and%20wealth%20in%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20means%20the%20federal%20government%20is%20the%20most%20important%20financial%20partner%20you%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20listen%2C%20if%20you%20feel%20behind%2C%20it's%20not%20the%20end%20of%20the%20world.%20Or%20maybe%20it%20is%2C%20but%20there%20are%20concrete%20steps%20you%20can%20take%20to%20try%20to%20get%20on%20more%20solid%20footing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20never%20too%20late%2C%26quot%3B%20Woods%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20best%20time%20to%20start%20saving%2C%20for%20many%20people%2C%20was%20when%20they%20were%20in%20their%20teens.%20The%20second-best%20time%20is%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-gen-z-millennials-uncertainty-fears-pensions-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712654821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661456f41caec1275a6df1ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-gen-z-millennials-uncertainty-fears-pensions-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Will%20I%20have%20enough%20to%20retire%3F%20It's%20an%20impossible%20question%20to%20answer%2C%20which%20makes%20retirement%20really%20scary%20for%20many.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-gen-z-millennials-uncertainty-fears-pensions-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BTS'%20'ON'%20Kinetic%20Manifesto%20Film%20goes%20viral%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712654387000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109160511%2Cimgsize-185190.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fk-pop%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fbts-on-kinetic-manifesto-film-achieves-600-million-views-on-youtube-becoming-their-13th-mv-to-achieve-the-feat%2Farticleshow%2F109160558.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F109160558.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98ON%E2%80%99%20now%20joins%20an%20illustrious%20lineup%20of%20BTS%20music%20videos%20that%20have%20crossed%20the%20600%20million%20view%20mark%2C%20including%20hits%20like%20%E2%80%98DNA%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Fire%E2%80