pcoming-project-124040900459_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-green-in-talks-to-raise-400-mn-in-offshore-loan-for-upcoming-project-124040900459_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-green-in-talks-to-raise-400-mn-in-offshore-loan-for-upcoming-project-124040900459_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20was%20put%20on%20an%20unfair%20PIP%20by%20my%20toxic%20manager.%20Here's%20how%20I%20fought%20it%20and%20went%20on%20to%20get%20promoted.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221199%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20walking%20on%20a%20tightrope%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660e7eb13f923f7dab047c35%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22899%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKeeping%20receipts%20and%20querying%20the%20validity%20of%20a%20PIP%20helped%20this%20worker%20keep%20their%20job%20and%20get%20promoted.%3Cp%3Ecienpies%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20this%20store%20manager%20at%20L'Oreal%20was%20asked%20to%20meet%20with%20her%20manager%20and%20HR%2C%20alarm%20bells%20went%20off.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20was%20put%20on%20a%20performance%20improvement%20plan%20she%20thought%20was%20unfair%20by%20a%20manager%20she%20found%20toxic.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20keeping%20receipts%20and%20not%20being%20afraid%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20yourself%20were%20key%20to%20surviving%20PIP.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20a%20former%20employee%20at%20L'Oreal%20who%20spoke%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20to%20protect%20their%20career.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20their%20employment%20at%20L'Oreal%20and%20their%20performance%20improvement%20plan.%20The%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20been%20working%20at%20L'Oreal%20for%20about%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20when%20I%20got%20an%20alarming%20text%20from%20my%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20was%20meeting%20with%20HR%20and%20asked%20me%20to%20come%20to%20a%20caf%C3%A9%20to%20speak%20with%20her%20afterward.%20I%20was%20a%20store%20manager%20at%20the%20time.%20When%20I%20arrived%20at%20the%20caf%C3%A9%2C%20the%20HR%20person%20was%20still%20sitting%20at%20the%20table.%20Alarm%20bells%20started%20going%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sat%20down%2C%20feeling%20confused.%20They%20pulled%20out%20this%20piece%20of%20paper%20and%20told%20me%3A%20%26quot%3BHere%20are%20all%20the%20things%20you've%20done%20wrong%2C%20and%20if%20you%20don't%20get%20your%20act%20together%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20let%20you%20go%20in%2030%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20shocked.%20I%20had%20always%20received%20good%20reviews%20and%20had%20been%20promoted%20to%20retail%20store%20manager%20three%20months%20before.%20It%20was%20bizarre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20PIP%20felt%20unwarranted%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20performance%20improvement%20plan%20felt%20like%20a%20reach.%20They%20couldn't%20tell%20me%20anything%20I%20was%20doing%20wrong%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20that%20the%20things%20on%20the%20PIP%20were%20made%20up.%20They%20just%20didn't%20feel%20worthy%20of%20being%20on%20a%20performance%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20I%20was%20given%20my%20PIP%20was%20because%20I%20hadn't%20trained%20the%20team%20for%20our%20store's%20reopening%20after%20recent%20renovations.%20My%20manager%20hadn't%20told%20me%20when%20the%20store%20was%20reopening%2C%20so%20I%20had%20yet%20to%20start%20the%20training.%20I%20had%20the%20receipts%20to%20prove%20all%20of%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20reason%20for%20the%20PIP%20was%20I%20had%20misspoken%20at%20an%20event.%20When%20the%20global%20president%20of%20L'Oreal%20asked%20me%20a%20question%20about%20sales%20I%20said%20the%20wrong%20figure%20in%20my%20jetlagged%20state.%20In%20the%20same%20moment%2C%20I%20checked%20my%20binder%2C%20where%20I%20had%20the%20correct%20figure%20written%20down%2C%20and%20quickly%20corrected%20myself.%20Having%20this%20instance%20as%20a%20reason%20for%20being%20put%20on%20PIP%20was%20ridiculous%20to%20me.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20only%20human.%20Can%20I%20not%20make%20one%20mistake%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20PIP%2C%20it%20said%20I%20need%20to%20retrain%20the%20team%20and%20give%20weekly%20status%20updates%20to%20my%20manager%20and%20my%20manager's%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20PIP%20should%20be%20a%20last%20resort%2C%20not%20a%20first%20warning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20manager%20at%20L'Oreal%2C%20I%20was%20told%20that%20a%20PIP%20should%20never%20be%20the%20first%20step.%20You%20should%20speak%20to%20the%20employee%20first%20and%20try%20to%20rectify%20the%20situation.%20If%20that%20doesn't%20work%2C%20the%20manager%20should%20pull%20in%20their%20manager%20to%20talk%20to%20the%20employee.%20If%20that%20still%20doesn't%20correct%20the%20behavior%2C%20you%20can%20start%20to%20think%20about%20a%20PIP.%20But%20in%20my%20case%2C%20it%20was%20the%20first%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20during%20the%20meeting%20not%20to%20try%20to%20justify%20myself%20to%20my%20manager.%20This%20felt%20more%20personal%20than%20performance-based%3A%20I%20would%20speak%20to%20HR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20reached%20out%20to%20HR%20after%20the%20PIP%20meeting%2C%20and%20started%20to%20send%20her%20all%20the%20receipts.%20Evidence%20that%20my%20boss%20and%20I%20had%20had%20meetings%20about%20the%20store%20reopening%2C%20where%20I%20updated%20her%20on%20progress.%20I%20also%20showed%20HR%20a%20document%20I'd%20made%20in%20preparation%20for%20the%20training%20before%20I'd%20known%20about%20the%20PIP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20issue%20highlighted%20in%20the%20PIP%20was%20I%20hadn't%20retrained%20staff%20in%20time%20for%20the%20store%20reopening.%20I%20wanted%20HR%20to%20understand%20I'd%20never%20been%20formally%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20two%20weeks%20of%20the%20PIP%2C%20it%20was%20checking%20boxes.%20Doing%20the%20weekly%20status%20updates%20and%20whatever%20they%20had%20asked%20me%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20PIP%20faded%20away%20once%20HR%20had%20the%20full%20story%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20HR%20had%20all%20the%20context%20and%20was%20made%20aware%20that%20this%20was%20the%20first%20time%20my%20boss%20had%20critiqued%20me%2C%20it%20just%20dissolved.%20I%20was%20on%20the%20PIP%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20month%20technically%2C%20but%20my%20plan%20wasn't%20spoken%20about%20again%20after%20the%20first%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EL'Oreal%20had%20a%20strict%20culture%20of%20%26quot%3BDon't%20tell%20anybody%20anything%2C%20ever.%26quot%3B%20I%20only%20told%20some%20of%20my%20closest%20work%20friends%2C%20and%20they%20were%20horrified.%20They%20thought%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20fired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20I%20was%20naive%2C%20but%20I%20never%20really%20took%20it%20as%20a%20death%20sentence%20because%20I%20knew%20it%20was%20unwarranted.%20I%20took%20it%20as%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20don't%20do%20these%20performative%20check-ins%2C%20then%20I%20was%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20fired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20PIP%20made%20me%20realize%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20move%20departments%20away%20from%20my%20toxic%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20was%20promoted%205%20times%20after%20my%20PIP%20and%20left%20as%20a%20global%20head%20of%20department%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20a%20year%20after%20this%20PIP%20happened%2C%20I%20was%20promoted%20out%20of%20the%20store%20into%20a%20corporate-level%20role.%20I%20was%20then%20working%20directly%20below%20my%20old%20manager's%20boss%2C%20whose%20boss%20is%20the%20president%20of%20L'Oreal%2C%20the%20same%20person%20I%20misquoted%20the%20sales%20number%20to.%20It%20became%20a%20joke%20between%20us%20about%20when%20they%20%26quot%3Btried%20to%20fire%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20get%20upset%20about%20this%20because%20it%20seemed%20so%20absurd.%20Years%20later%2C%20I%20discovered%20that%20my%20then-boss%20was%20under%20pressure%20from%20her%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20on%20to%20be%20promoted%20another%20four%20times%20over%20six%20years.%20I%20left%20the%20company%20as%20the%20global%20head%20of%20my%20department.%20My%20salary%20had%20tripled%20since%20I%20was%20on%20PIP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20advise%20anyone%20worried%20about%20being%20put%20on%20PIP%20to%20document%20everything.%20Have%20all%20your%20receipts%20and%20emails%20so%20you%20can%20stand%20up%20for%20yourself%20if%20you're%20put%20on%20PIP%20unfairly.%20Don't%20be%20afraid%20to%20take%20matters%20into%20your%20own%20hands%20%E2%80%94%20and%20remember%20that%20PIP%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20a%20death%20sentence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fput-on-pip-fought-back-won-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712654086000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660e838416bde8d4ead588b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fput-on-pip-fought-back-won-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20manager%20at%20L'Oreal%20was%20put%20on%20a%20performance%20improvement%20plan%20she%20felt%20was%20unfair.%20She%20fought%20back%20and%20stayed%20with%20the%20company%20for%20several%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Daisy%20Schofield)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fput-on-pip-fought-back-won-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20went%20from%20making%20%2415K%20to%20nearly%20%24700K%20over%20my%20career%20at%20Oracle%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20Meta.%20Here's%20how%20I%20incre