pees%2C%20or%20%2415%2C000%2C%20was%20low%20compared%20to%20what%20new%20grads%20were%20making%20at%20that%20time%20in%20competing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-salaries-what-you-make-google-apple-amazon-meta-ibm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBig%20Tech%20companies%20like%20Microsoft%20or%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20it%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Btake%20it%20or%20leave%20it%26quot%3B%20new%20grad%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20work%20was%20unappealing%20to%20me%20because%20it%20didn't%20align%20with%20my%20career%20interests%20%E2%80%94%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20continue%20building%20expertise%20in%20that%20specific%20area%20of%20software%20engineering%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20took%20it%20to%20get%20my%20foot%20in%20the%20door%20of%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company%20and%20build%20credibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20I%20eventually%20wanted%20to%20end%20up%20where%20all%20the%20action%20is%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-history-technology-industry-animated-timeline-video-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESilicon%20Valley%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20worked%20at%20Oracle%20from%202012%20to%202014%2C%20and%20during%20this%20time%2C%20I%20applied%20to%20graduate%20schools%20in%20the%20US%20because%20I%20felt%20a%20formal%20computer%20science%20degree%20would%20help%20me%20compete%20with%20the%20talented%20people%20in%20the%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20accepted%20into%20a%20graduate%20program%20in%20computer%20science%20at%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20University%20in%C2%A0Pittsburgh.%20I%20left%20behind%20my%20family%20and%20friends%20in%20India%20and%20moved%20to%20the%20US%20with%20nothing%20but%20a%20suitcase%20and%20%2465%2C000%20in%20student%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrad%20school%20was%20hard%2C%20but%20the%20doors%20it%20opened%20for%20me%20made%20the%C2%A0struggle%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20ecstatic%20to%20get%20a%20job%20at%20Apple%3C%2Fstr