0let%20your%20bad%20salary%20%26quot%3Bbaggage%26quot%3B%20carry%20over%20to%20your%20new%20job.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20salary%20isn't%20up%20to%20market%20standards%20right%20now%2C%20don't%20let%20it%20affect%20your%20pay%20at%20the%20next%20job.%20Otherwise%2C%20it'll%20lead%20to%20a%20cycle%20where%20you'll%20be%20underpaid%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20and%20recruiters%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-administration-wants-close-wage-gap-more-pay-transparency-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euse%20your%20salary%20history%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20give%20you%20only%20a%20modest%20raise%2C%20while%20your%20actual%20market%20value%20could%20easily%20be%20double%20or%20triple%20your%20most%20recent%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20California%2C%20labor%20laws%20make%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dir.ca.gov%2Fdlse%2Fcalifornia_equal_pay_act.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eillegal%20for%20employers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20ask%20you%20about%20your%20current%20salary%20and%20salary%20history.%20You're%20also%20allowed%20to%20ask%20potential%20employers%20for%20the%20pay%20range%20for%20the%C2%A0position%20you're%20applying%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20state%20has%20similar%20protections%2C%20just%20being%20aware%20of%20this%20law%20can%20help%20you%20make%C2%A0any%20corrections%20to%20your%20pay%20during%20negotiations.%20This%20helped%20me%20start%20offer%20negotiations%20from%20my%C2%A0market%20value%20instead%20of%20my%20current%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Sometimes%2C%20you%20have%20to%20take%20a%20leap%20of%20faith%20to%20make%20that%2010x%20impact%20on%20your%20career.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20involve%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-switch-careers-tech-entry-jobs-developer-software-engineer-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eswitching%20from%20a%20non-tech%20job%20to%20a%20tech%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20taking%20a%20short-term%20hit%20for%20long-term%20gain.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20picked%20Oracle%20for%20my%20first%20job%20despite%20the%20low%20pay%20and%20unappealing%20work%20so%20I%20could%20build%20credibility%20to%20get%20into%20a%20Tier%201%20grad%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20took%20a%20loan%20of%20about%20%2465%2C000%20to%20pay%20for%20Carnegie%20Mellon%2C%20even%20though%20I%20could%20have%20chosen%20to%20go%20to%20a%20cheaper%20public%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeciding%20to%20work%20at%20Oracle%20and%20attend%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20cost%20me%20a%20few%20years%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20debt%2C%20but%20doing%20so%20opened%20doors%20unlike%20anything%20else%2C%20and%20I%20haven't%20looked%20back%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Negotiate%20to%20keep%20your%20base%20salary%20from%20falling%20behind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20inevitable%20for%20your%20salary%20to%20fall%20behind%20as%20you%20stay%20longer%20at%20a%20company%2C%20especially%20in%20tech%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-it-means-to-be-offered-stock-options-2015-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erestricted%20stock%20unit%20(RSU)%20%26quot%3Bcliffs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20RSU%20packages%20offered%20to%20new%20employees%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%20have%20a%20two-%20to%20four-year%20vesting%20period.%20Unless%20the%20employer%20offers%20a%20significant%20pay%20bump%20along%20the%20way%2C%20total%20compensation%20usually%20takes%20a%20drop%20after%20this%20vesting%20period.%20Many%20companies%20also%20offer%20annual%20performance-based%20stock%20refreshers%20to%C2%A0lower%20this%20salary%20gap%2C%20but%20they're%20usually%20not%20as%20large%20as%20the%20initial%20grant.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20love%20working%20at%20your%20company%20and%20feel%20forced%20to%20move%20just%20to%20get%20a%20raise%2C%20you%20can%20ask%20your%20senior%20leadership%20to%20make%