%3E%3Cli%3EWhile%20the%20new%20Model%203%20comes%20with%20better%20materials%20and%20a%20fresh%20interior%2C%20it%20lost%20its%20tax%20credit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20says%20the%20more%20spacious%20Model%20Y%2C%20which%20is%20still%20eligible%20for%20a%20tax%20credit%2C%20is%20the%20better%20buy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-model-3-best-features-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2017%20Tesla%20Model%203%3C%2Fa%3E%20changed%20the%20EV%20game.%20Offering%20rapid%20acceleration%2C%20plenty%20of%20range%2C%20and%20a%20somewhat%20affordable%20price%2C%20the%20Model%203%20squashed%20most%20preconceived%20notions%20about%20what%20electric%20cars%20should%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20original%20one%20didn't%20come%20without%20flaws.%20From%20noisy%20cabins%20to%20build%20quality%20woes%2C%20the%20early%20Model%203s%20excelled%20in%20some%20areas%20but%20lacked%20in%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20shortcomings%2C%20I%20was%20allured%20by%20the%20Model%203.%20Last%20year%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbought-used-tesla-model-3-high-mileage-happy-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epicked%20up%20a%20used%202019%20model%20for%20around%20%2426%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20have%20enjoyed%20my%20time%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20Model%203's%20relatively%20long%20lifecycle%20without%20any%20significant%20updates%2C%20the%20refreshed%202024%20Model%203%20has%20been%20long-awaited.%20The%20day%20Tesla%20Charlotte%20began%20demo%20drives%20of%20the%20new%20Model%203%2C%20I%20signed%20up%20for%20a%20slot%20to%20see%20if%20it%20was%20different%20enough%20from%20the%20outgoing%20one%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-model-y-redesign-what-could-change-features-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewarrant%20an%20upgrade%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETesla's%20approach%20to%20vehicle%20production%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20consumer%20probably%20couldn't%20tell%20the%20difference%20between%20a%202017%20and%20a%202023%20Model%203.%20Tesla's%20upgrade%20approach%20involves%20tiny%20alterations%20%E2%80%94%20like%20making%20the%20trunk%20power-operated%2C%20installing%20beefier%20computers%2C%20and%20implementing%20features%20like%20a%20heated%20steering%20wheel%20%E2%80%94%20on%20a%20frequent%20but%20non-set%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20the%20changes%20were%20improvements%2C%20though.%20One%20controversial%20revision%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-uptick-crashes-accidents-elon-musk-removed-radar-autopilot-report-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremoving%20the%20ultrasonic%20parking%20sensors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20many%20owners%20disliked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20Model%203%20got%20more%20of%20a%20facelift%20than%20previous%20versions.%20It%20offers%20a%20new%20front%20and%20rear%20appearance%2C%20though%20the%20side-view%20is%20largely%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Model%203's%20new%20look%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22close-up%20of%20the%20nose%20of%20a%20black%20Tesla%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6614107d3f923f7dab05799b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20nose%20of%20the%202024%20Tesla%20Model%203.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lambrecht%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Model%203%20is%20a%20much%20more%20eye-catching%20car%20than%20the%20outgoing%20one.%20It%20offers%20sharper%20headlights%2C%20a%20chiseled%20front%20nose%2C%20and%20aggressive%20split-cut%20rear%20taillights%20that%20alert%20other%20motorists%20you're%20merging%20left%20with%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20door%20handles%20are%20the%20same%2C%20but%20now%20the%20doors%20carry%20a%20heft%20that%20pre-2021%20examples%20could%20only%20dream%20of.%20When%20you%20close%20the%20doors%2C%20you%20hear%20a%20confident%20thud.%20Is%20it%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faudi-e-tron-gt-electric-sedan-performance-horsepower-specs-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAudi%20e-tron%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20closing%20the%20door%20feels%20like%20you're%20sealing%20off%20a%20bank%20vault%3F%20No%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20great%20improvement%20for%20Tesla's%20entry-level%20vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20common%20theme%20in%20the%20new%20Model%203%20is%20better-quality%20materials%2C%20both%20for%20feel%20and%20sound.%20The%20rear%20trunk%20insert%20and%20door%20sill%20pockets%20are%20made%20of%20carpeting%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20plastic%20in%20older%20versions.%20Not%20only%20does%20it%20feel%20better%20but%20softer%20and%20squishier%20materials%20also%20help%20reduce%20rattling%20and%20vibrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20windows%20are%20now%20composed%20of%20acoustic%20glass%2C%20which%20is%20two%20layers%20of%20glass%20laminated%20together%20with%20a%20membrane%20in%20the%20middle%20that%20helps%20absorb%20sound%20waves%2C%20minimizing%20the%203's%20once%20echo-ey%20cabin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EInside%20the%20fresh%20interior%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22inside%20the%20Tesla%20Model%203%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661410e33f923f7dab057a2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%202024%20Tesla%20Model%203's%20new%20cabin%20features%20a%20wrap-around%20light%20bar.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lambrecht%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20thing%20that%20sticks%20out%20when%20you%20sit%20in%20the%20driver's%20seat%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20any%20stalks.%20The%20previous%20Model%203%20had%20two%20stalks%20behind%20the%20steering%20wheel%20%E2%80%94%20one%20for%20turn%20signals%20and%20the%20other%20for%20selecting%20drive%2C%20reverse%2C%20or%20park.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20blinkers%20have%20been%20moved%20to%20haptic%20steering%20wheel%20buttons.%20The%20drive%20selector%20is%20now%20a%20vertical%20strip%20on%20the%20left%20side%20of%20the%20screen.%20When%20you've%20stopped%2C%20you%20simply%20press%20the%20park%20icon%20to%20put%20the%20car%20in%20park.%20I%20thought%20the%20blinker%20buttons%20were%20cool%2C%20but%20others%20may%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20made%20some%20overwhelmingly%20positive%20changes%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20interior.%20The%20base%20version%20has%20a%20nine-speaker%20audio%20system%2C%20and%20the%20Long%20Range%20features%20a%2017-speaker%20system%20with%20two%20subwoofers.%20The%20nine-speaker%20version%20is%20an%20improvement%20from%20the%20old%20base%20system%2C%20which%20was%20already%20pleasant%20to%20listen%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20Model%203%20comes%20with%20heated%20and%20ventilated%20front%20seats%20as%20standard.%20Complementing%20the%20new%20seats%20is%20a%20sharp%20and%20distinctive%20ambient%20light%20strip%20that%20encircles%20the%20driver%20and%20passenger%20and%20extends%20to%20the%20rear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20screen%20in%20the%20backseat%20of%20the%202024%20Tesla%20Model%203%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66141bfe3f923f7dab0587d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20screen%20in%20the%20backseat.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lambrecht%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBackseat%20occupants%20get%20an%208-inch%20center%20display%2C%20which%20allows%20them%20to%20play%20games%20and%20activate%20the%20seat%20heaters.%20Tesla%20also%20reworked%20the%20rear%20air%20vents%2C%20so%20the%20direction%20and%20speed%20are%20now%20controlled%20through%20the%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EImproved%20ride%20quality%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20wheel%20on%20a%20Tesla%20model%203%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661414681caec1275a6dba99%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%202024%20Model%203%20gets%20new%20tires%20and%20updated%20wheel%20designs.%20If%20you%20like%20a%20better%20quality%20ride%2C%20stick%20with%20the%20smaller%2018-inch%20wheels%20(as%20pictured).%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lambrecht%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20outgoing%20Model%203%20drove%20well%2C%20though%20it%20lagged%20in%20the%20noise%2C%20vibration%2C%20and%20harshness%20(NVH)%20category.%20Excessive%20road%20noise%2C%20vibrations%20on%20certain%20road%20surfaces%2C%20and%20occasional%20creaks%20and%20rattles%20impeded%20the%20Model%203's%20otherwise%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-owners-share-perks-best-features-electric-car-ev-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esilent%20driving%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20Model%203%20felt%20quieter%20on%20the%20road%2C%20and%20the%20updated%20suspension%20soaked%20up%20road%20imperfections%20more%20eloquently.%20Whenever%20I%20drove%20over%20a%20bump%2C%20the%20shock%20no%20longer%20permeated%20throughout%20the%20entirety%20of%20the%20cabin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20comfort-tuned%20suspension%20resulted%20in%20more%20body%20roll%20when%20pushed%20through%20corners%2C%20though.%20Moreover%2C%20when%20you%20floor%20the%20accelerator%2C%20the%20car's%20nose%20now%20lifts%20upwards.%20Overall%2C%20the%20ride%20felt%20substantially%20more%20refined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EZero%20to%2060%20in%205.8%20Seconds%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223995%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20back%20of%20a%20black%20Tesla%20Model%203%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661414b21caec1275a6dbb19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222996%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%202024%20Model%203%20has%20five%20color%20options%2C%20though%20only%20Stealth%20Gray%20Metallic%20is%20included.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lambrecht%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20base%20rear-wheel%20drive%20(RWD)%20version%20I%20tested%20had%20plenty%20of%20power%20to%20accelerate.%20Tesla%20says%20it%20should%20go%20from%20zero%20to%2060%20in%205.8%20seconds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20crave%20the%20sensation%20of%20accelerative%20force%2C%20Tesla%20offers%20a%20Dual%20Motor%20version%20with%20a%20larger%20battery%20and%20an%20additional%20motor%20up%20front.%20This%20one%20is%20much%20quicker%2C%20offering%20a%20zero-to-60%20time%20of%204.2%20seconds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPricing%20and%20range%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20interior%20of%20a%20Tesla%20model%203%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6614154316bde8d4ead68b09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%202024%20Tesla%20Model%203's%20front%20seats%20are%20a%20big%20upgrade%20over%20last%20year's%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lambrecht%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20Model%203%20RWD%20starts%20at%20%2440%2C630%20with%20a%20272-mile%20range.%20The%20Long%20Range%20Dual%20Motor%20version%20costs%20%248%2C000%20more%2C%20running%20%2448%2C630%20with%20341%20miles%20of%20EPA-estimated%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20Tesla%20Model%203's%20sticker%20price%20didn't%20increase%20with%20the%20updates%2C%20but%20it%20no%20longer%20qualifies%20for%20the%20federal%20tax%20credit%20due%20to%20battery%20mineral%20sourcing%20requirements%20courtesy%20of%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20(IRA).%20Last%20year's%20version%20was%20effectively%20%247%2C500%20less%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20spacious%20Model%20Y%20still%20gets%20the%20credit%2C%20so%20it's%20actually%20less%20expensive%20than%20the%20Model%203.%20The%202024%20Tesla%20Model%20Y%20RWD%2C%20which%20offers%20some%20260%20miles%20of%20range%2C%20starts%20at%20%2445%2C630%2C%20meaning%20it'll%20run%20%2438%2C130%20when%20the%20credit%20is%20applied.%20While%20it%20doesn't%20have%20ventilated%20seats%20or%20a%20rear%20screen%2C%20I%20would%20take%20the%20Model%20Y%20over%20the%203%20for%20the%20practicality%20and%20cost%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EVerdict%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20steering%20wheel%20on%20a%20Tesla%20Model%203%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661415c43f923f7dab0580f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENo%20turn%20signal%20stocks%20or%20a%20physical%20drive%20selector%20will%20take%20a%20bit%20to%20get%20used%20to.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lambrecht%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20Tesla%20Model%203%20is%20a%20massive%20improvement%20over%20the%20outgoing%20one.%20Its%20new%20luxury%20features%20and%20improved%20build%20quality%20make%20Tesla's%20compact%20sedan%20a%20worthy%20opponent%20of%20higher-end%20luxury%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20leaving%20the%20driver's%20seat%2C%20I%20quite%20liked%20the%20new%20Model%203's%20feature%20list%2C%20but%20I%20think%20the%20less%20refined%20but%20more%20spacious%20Model%20Y%20is%20the%20better%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2024-tesla-model-3-improved-features-model-y-better-option-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712653621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6614338f16bde8d4ead6a9e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2024-tesla-model-3-improved-features-model-y-better-option-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%202024%20Tesla%20Model%203%20has%20improvements%20from%20the%20outgoing%20model%2C%20but%20it's%20no%20longer%20eligible%20for%20the%20%247%2C500%20federal%20tax%20credit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22andrewl20033%40gmail.com%20(Andrew%20Lambrecht)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2024-tesla-model-3-improved-features-model-y-better-option-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Jamie%20Dimon%20manifesto%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jamie%20Dimon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6614564f3f923f7dab05b366%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FAlex%20Brandon%3B%20iStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%202023%20shareholder%20letter%20from%C2%A0JPMorgan%20Chase%20CEO%C2%A0Jamie%20Dimon%20is%20chock%20full%20of%20policy%20ideas.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDimon's%20letter%20focuses%20on%20global%20peace%2C%20rethinking%20trade%20alliances%2C%20and%20addressing%20domestic%20unrest.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20CEO%20proposed%20policy%20changes%20to%20improve%20economic%20equality%20and%20bolster%20the%20Earned%20Income%20Tax%20Credit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20robust%20new%20policy%20platform%20just%20dropped%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20not%20from%20either%20leading%20presidential%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-career%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJamie%20Dimon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20billionaire%20CEO%20of%20JPMorgan%20Chase%2C%20outlined%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20issues%20facing%20the%20company%2C%20the%20country%2C%20and%20the%20world%20in%20his%202023%20annual%20shareholder%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimon's%20manifesto%20touches%20on%20everything%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-jpmorgan-ai-extraordinary-consequences-transformative-internet-electricity-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-jpmorgan-letter-war-inflation-recession-rates-economy-ai-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egeopolitics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20includes%20a%20strong%20emotional%20appeal%20to%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20US%20in%20bringing%20the%20West%20together%20in%20a%20time%20of%20global%20turbulence.%20Though%20Dimon's%20annual%20letters%20do%20usually%20address%20policy%2C%20this%20year's%20is%20much%20thicker%20than%20usual%2C%20an%20intriguing%20turn%20from%20a%20consequential%20business%20leader%20who's%20eyed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-ceo-jamie-dimon-considers-politics-bill-ackman-president-election-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20future%20in%20politics%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20Dimon%20is%20presenting%20a%20suite%20of%20policy%20proposals%20on%20how%20to%20bolster%20everything%20from%20the%20US'%20international%20influence%20to%20improving%20the%20lots%20of%20America's%20low-income%20population.%20It's%20a%20letter%20that%20affirms%20Dimon's%20views%20on%20American%20exceptionalism%2C%20and%20the%20ways%20that%20policy%20needs%20to%20evolve%20to%20drive%20that%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EStrength%20on%20the%20world%20stage%2C%20starting%20with%20aid%20for%20Ukraine%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%20theme%20in%20Dimon's%20letter%20is%20how%20important%20global%20peace%20is%20to%20furthering%20America's%20ambitions%2C%20and%20that%20the%20US%20should%20use%20its%20power%20and%20influence%20to%20ensure%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20he%20points%20to%20American%20leadership%20as%20crucial%20in%20resolving%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUkraine's%20struggle%20is%20our%20struggle%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-will-lose-war-russia-congress-funding-not-approved-zelenskyy-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtrast%20to%20current%20Republican%20demands%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Dimon%20says%20that%20Ukraine%20requires%20the%20US's%20help%20%26quot%3Bimmediately%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20it's%20key%20to%20realize%20that%20US%20aid%20to%20Ukraine%20will%20flow%20back%20into%20the%20American%20economy%20as%20many%20of%20the%20weapons%20and%20equipment%20used%20are%20made%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20he%20emphasizes%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20West%20needing%20%26quot%3Bunquestioned%20military%20might.%26quot%3B%20Like%20many%20others%2C%20he%20may%20have%20been%20rattled%20by%20Oppenheimer%3A%20%26quot%3BMost%20important%2C%20the%20specter%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20%E2%80%94%20probably%20still%20the%20greatest%20threat%20to%20mankind%20%E2%80%94%20hovers%20as%20the%20ultimate%20decider%2C%20which%20should%20strike%20deep%20fear%20in%20all%20our%20hearts%2C%26quot%3B%20Dimon%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20says%20that%20the%20US%20needs%20to%20flex%20its%20other%20muscles%20of%20power%20%E2%80%94%20economic%20policy%2C%20diplomacy%2C%20and%20intelligence%20%E2%80%94%20beyond%20military%20strength.%20And%20the%20US%20also%20needs%20to%20keep%20its%20citizenry%20informed%20on%20why%20it's%20so%20important%20for%20the%20US%20to%20get%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERethinking%20global%20trade%20alliances%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDimon%20said%20that%20just%20as%20the%20West%20reimagines%20its%20military%20alliances%20and%20strategies%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20start%20doing%20the%20same%20for%20economics.%20And%20that%20means%20that%20while%20the%20West%20perhaps%20overlooked%20China%20at%20its%20own%20peril%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20%26quot%3Bjust%20fix%20it.%26quot%3B%20It%20also%20means%20that%20the%20US%20should%20%26quot%3Bthoughtfully%26quot%3B%20engage%20with%20China%20%E2%80%94%20sans%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDone%20properly%2C%20such%20a%20strategy%20would%20help%20strengthen%2C%20coalesce%20and%20possibly%20be%20the%20glue%20that%20holds%20together%20Western%20democratic%20alliances%20over%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20Dimon%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20believes%20that%20the%20US%20should%20reenter%20the%20Trans-Pacific%20Partnership%20Agreement%2C%20which%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tpp-trans-pacific-partnership-what-it-means-2017-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epulled%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20early%20into%20his%20tenure%20in%20order%20to%20instead%20focus%20on%20one-on-one%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Dimon%20writes%20that%20industrial%20policy%20has%20proven%20to%20be%20necessary%20to%20bolster%20industries%20needed%20for%20national%20security%20like%20semiconductors%20and%20rare%20earth%20minerals%2C%20it%20should%20have%20a%20very%20limited%20government%20role.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20government%20should%20only%20be%20able%20to%20touch%20specific%20things%20like%20tax%20credits%2C%20in%20his%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20industrial%20policy%20should%20have%20what%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3Btwin%20provisions%26quot%3B%3A%20Both%20limitations%20on%20political%20interference%2C%20which%20includes%20social%20policies%2C%20and%20improved%20permitting%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20broadly%2C%20Dimon%20thinks%20it%20might%20be%20time%20to%20have%20an%20even%20larger%20rethinking%20of%20international%20rules%20and%20structure.%20He%20envisions%20this%20as%20potentially%20a%20new%2C%20%26quot%3Breimagined%26quot%3B%20Bretton%20Woods%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreservehistory.org%2Fessays%2Fbretton-woods-created%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eagreement%20that%20originally%20created%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'The%20fraying%20of%20the%20American%20dream'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDimon%20identifies%20two%20key%20issues%20driving%20domestic%20unrest%20%E2%80%94%20stagnation%20on%20border%20security%20and%20%26quot%3Bthe%20fraying%20of%20the%20American%20dream.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20believes%20that%20Congress%20should%20act%20on%20border%20control%20and%20that%20there%20should%20be%20a%20push%20for%20policies%20to%20drive%20economic%20growth.%20He%20believes%20that%20citizens%20losing%20trust%20in%20the%20government%20is%20%26quot%3Bdamaging%20to%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20it's%20time%20for%20action%20to%20help%20the%20government%20be%20able%20to%20act%20quickly%20and%20with%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20to%20be%20fair%2C%20business%20could%20use%20its%20influence%20to%20do%20less%20to%20further%20its%20own%20interest%20and%20more%20to%20enhance%20the%20nation%20as%20a%20whole%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimon%20points%20to%20the%20growth%20in%20wage%20inequality%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bwrong%26quot%3B%20policy%20falls%20disproportionately%20on%20the%20backs%20of%20lower-earning%20Americans.%20Dimon%20said%20that%20he%20believes%20all%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20even%20%26quot%3Bstarter%20jobs%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20should%20be%20treated%20with%20respect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20endorses%20two%20policy%20levers%20to%20help%20improve%20economic%20equality.%20First%2C%20he%20believes%20that%20educational%20institutions%20should%20be%20scrutinized%20on%20the%20incomes%20and%20job%20quality%20of%20their%20graduates%20(or%20non-graduates).%20Jobs%20skills%20training%20is%20paramount%20to%20helping%20close%20the%20mismatch%20between%20unemployed%20workers%20and%20the%20roles%20that%20are%20hiring%2C%20according%20to%20Dimon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20already%20spend%20a%20tremendous%20amount%20of%20money%20on%20education%20%E2%80%94%20just%20not%20the%20right%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Dimon%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20piece%20of%20the%20puzzle%20Dimon%20recommends%20is%20one%20that%20Congress%20could%20take%20up%3A%20Bolstering%20the%20Earned%20Income%20Tax%20Credit%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexpansion-tax-credits-good-step-leave-out-americans-in-need-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEITC%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20a%20credit%20aimed%20at%20lower-income%20families%20that%20was%20enhanced%20under%20the%20American%20Rescue%20Plan.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Dimon's%20vision%2C%20that%20credit%20would%20be%20available%20to%20all%20lower-income%20workers%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0without%20proration%20for%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildless-adults-earned-income-tax-credit-eitc-eligible-arp-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithout%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20turned%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Bnegative%20income%20payroll%20tax%2C%20paid%20monthly.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20potentially%20take%20the%20form%20of%20monthly%20checks%20or%20a%20paycheck%20boost.%20Dimon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-tax-rich-people-more-help-lower-income-people-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20taxes%20on%20the%20wealthy%20could%20help%20offset%20the%20costs%20of%20bolstering%20the%20EITC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimon%20closes%20out%20the%20policy%20portion%20of%20his%20letter%20by%20reiterating%20that%2C%20while%20the%20US%20has%20%26quot%3Bcomplex%20and%20difficult%20tasks%20ahead%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20hopes%20to%20see%20a%20future%20where%20the%20US%20is%20able%20to%20rise%20to%20the%20challenges%20facing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20remain%20with%20a%20deep%20and%20abiding%20faith%20in%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20enduring%20values%20of%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-shareholder-letter-manifesto-us-exceptionalism-policy-trade-ukraine-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712653441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6614564f3f923f7dab05b366%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-shareholder-letter-manifesto-us-excep