-caste-census-5378978%5C%22%3Ejobs-led%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20by%20turning%20the%20country%20into%20a%20manufacturing%20powerhouse.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20though%20the%20BJP%20is%20yet%20to%20release%20its%20manifesto%2C%20PM%20Modi%20has%20promised%20to%20make%20India%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Findian-economy-gdp-india-to-be-3rd-largest-economy-by-2027-surpass-japan-germany-jefferies-5105312%5C%22%3Ethird-largest%20economy%20in%20his%20third%20term%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpm-modi-pledges-to-make-india-developed-country-by-2047-amit-shah-5097180%5C%22%3Edeveloped%20one%20by%202047.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20has%20been%20written%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fyou-will-always-remain-a-hero-mallikarjun-kharge-writes-to-manmohan-singh-on-his-retirement-from-rajya-sabha-5362242%5C%22%3EManmohan%20Singh%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Modi%20regimes.%20This%20piece%20will%20focus%20on%20how%20economic%20performance%2C%20mainly%20GDP%20growth%20(average%20numbers%20used%20everywhere)%20and%20inflation%2C%20correlates%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20results.%20We%20analyse%20data%20from%20the%201971-77%20election%20cycle%20onwards%20as%20before%20that%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20in%20power%20uninterruptedly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E1977%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDuring%20the%201971-1977%20tenure%20of%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20the%20GDP%20growth%20was%202.7%25%2C%20much%20less%20than%20the%205.7%25%20recorded%20in%20her%20previous%20term%20in%201967-71.%20She%20went%20on%20to%20face%20a%20defeat%20in%20elections%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20the%20first-ever%20non-Congress%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E1980%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%201977-80%2C%20the%20Janata%20Party%20government%20delivered%20a%20GDP%20growth%20of%202.6%25%2C%20just%200.1%20percentage%20points%20lower%20than%20its%20predecessor.%20It%20faced%20a%20rout%20in%20the%201980%20general%20elections%2C%20though%20the%20party%20had%20split%20due%20to%20differences%20within%20the%20top%20leadership.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E1984%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20During%201980-1985%2C%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20recorded%20a%20higher%20GDP%20growth%20of%205.5%25%2C%20though%20her%20tenure%20was%20cut%20short%20when%20she%20was%20assassinated%20in%201984.%20The%20Congress%20went%20on%20to%20win%20big%20in%20the%20general%20elections%20that%20year%2C%20helped%20by%20a%20sympathy%20factor.%20To%20note%2C%20elections%20were%20held%20in%20the%20last%20week%20of%20December%201984%2C%20instead%20of%20three%20quarters%2C%20all%20four%20quarters%20in%20the%20financial%20year%20have%20been%20attributed%20to%20Indira%20Gandhi%20for%20ease%20of%20analysis).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E1989%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20delivered%20a%20higher%20GDP%20growth%20of%205.9%25%20in%201985-1989%2C%20but%20he%20was%20still%20defeated%20in%20the%201989%20polls%2C%20in%20large%20part%20due%20to%20the%20Bofors%20scandal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E1991%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Janata%20Dal%20years%20under%20V.P.%20Singh%20and%20later%20Chandra%20Shekhar%20registered%20a%20lower%20GDP%20growth%20of%205.7%25.%20Their%20government%20was%20ultimately%20voted%20out%2C%20though%20also%20helped%20by%20the%20sympathy%20generated%20for%20the%20Congress%20after%20Rajiv%20Gandhi's%20assassination.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E1996%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20father%20of%20economic%20reforms%2C%20P.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20achieved%20a%20GDP%20growth%20rate%20of%205.1%25%20between%201991%20and%201996%2C%20slightly%20lower%20than%20what%20the%20government%20preceding%20him%20could%20achieve.%20Rao's%20government%20went%20on%20to%20face%20a%20defeat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E1998%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%201996-98%2C%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20governments%20led%20by%20H.D.%20Deve%20Gowda%20and%20I.K.%20Gujral%20registered%20a%20higher%20growth%20of%205.8%25%20but%20still%20lost%20due%20to%20instability.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E1999%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20government%20saw%20a%20higher%20growth%20of%206.2%25%20in%201998-99%20and%20it%20won%20the%20snap%20polls%20precipitated%20by%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20Jayalalithaa's%20support.%20Vajpayee%20eventually%20lost%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20by%20one%20vote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E2004%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20At%205.8%25%2C%20the%C2%A0GDP%20growth%20during%201999-2004%20was%20lower.%20Vajpayee%20lost%20despite%20his%20'India%20Shining'%20campaign.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E2009%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20UPA-I%20in%202004-09%20achieved%20higher%20GDP%20growth%20of%206.9%25%2C%20thanks%20partly%20to%20the%20base%20set%20by%20Vajpayee%2C%20and%20went%20on%20to%20win%20a%20second%20term.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E2014%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20During%202009-14%2C%20Manmohan%20Singh%20in%20his%20second%20term%20delivered%20a%20lower%20growth%20of%206.7%25%20and%20lost%20the%20election.%20This%20was%20also%20a%20period%20of%20high%20inflation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E2019%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Narendra%20Modi%20delivered%20a%20higher%20GDP%20growth%20of%207.4%25%20in%202014-2019%20and%20was%20accorded%20a%20second%20term%20by%20voters.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E2024%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOver%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20according%20to%20available%20data%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20seen%20lower%20growth%20compared%20to%20its%20first%20term%2C%20in%20large%20part%20due%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20above%20data%20shows%20that%20a%20government%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20voted%20out%20whenever%20GDP%20growth%20under%20it%20is%20lower%20compared%20to%20its%20predecessor's.%20This%20happened%20six%20times%2C%20in%201977%2C%201980%2C%201991%2C%201996%2C%202004%20and%202014.%20In%20contrast%2C%20governments%20that%20managed%20to%20improve%20the%20country's%20growth%20rate%20went%20on%20to%20win%20four%20times%2C%20in%201984%2C%201999%2C%202009%20and%202019%2C%20though%20they%20also%20lost%20twice%20in%201989%20and%201998.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20inflation%20and%20electoral%20outcomes%20do%20not%20indicate%20any%20clear%20correlation.%20Governments%20that%20have%20recorded%20lower%20inflation%20have%20lost%20four%20out%20of%20six%20times%20in%201977%2C%201989%2C%201996%20and%202014%2C%20despite%20a%20better%20performance%20on%20the%20front.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20governments%20with%20higher%20inflation%20have%20also%20been%20punished%20in%20four%20out%20of%20six%20elections%2C%20in%201980%2C%201991%2C%201998%20and%202004.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Narendra%20Modi%20government's%20first%20term%20was%20marked%20by%20low%20inflation.%20During%20this%20period%2C%20the%20general%20consumer%20price%20index%20(CPI)%20rose%20by%20an%20average%20of%204.3%25%20per%20year.%20However%2C%20its%20second%20term%20has%20seen%20CPI%20inflation%20average%205.77%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorldwide%2C%20given%20the%20ravages%20of%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20and%20the%20possibility%20that%20people%20have%20been%20more%20forgiving%2C%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%20have%20witnessed%20governments%20delivering%20lower%20growth%20returning%20to%20power%20in%20a%20few%20countries.%20This%20was%20seen%20in%20Turkey%20and%20Canada%2C%20though%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20lost%20the%20Presidential%20Polls%20in%202020.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20how%20inflation%20and%20economic%20growth%20affect%20the%20Modi%20government's%20prospects%20in%20the%20upcoming%20elections%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Amitabh%20Tiwari%20is%20a%20political%20strategist%20and%20commentator.%20In%20his%20earlier%20avatar%2C%20he%20was%20a%20corporate%20