anath%20%E2%80%94%20a%20civil%20engineer%20and%20urban%20planner%20with%20more%20than%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20water%20and%20sanitation%20sector%20%E2%80%94%20has%20previously%20worked%20on%20the%20Karnataka%20Water%20Policy%20in%202019.%20He%20is%20also%20a%20Trustee%20of%20the%20Biome%20Environmental%20Trust%2C%20a%20Bengaluru-based%20non-profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20424px)%20100vw%2C%20424px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FS-Vishwanath-1712314633.png%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22424%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Solutions%20to%20Bengaluru's%20water%20scarcity%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FS-Vishwanath-1712314633.png%20424w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FS-Vishwanath-1712314633-200x300.png%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FS-Vishwanath-1712314633-150x225.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-346647%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22636%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ES%20Vishwanath%2C%20aka%20%E2%80%98Zenrainman%E2%80%99%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20how%20would%20he%20define%20the%20current%20crisis%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEssentially%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20state.%20If%20you%20build%20your%20piped%20water%20network%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20city%2C%20then%20there%20will%20be%20less%20pressure%20on%20your%20aquifers%2C%20and%20there%20will%20be%20no%20need%20to%20draw%20groundwater.%20Your%20borewells%20will%20have%20water%20and%20there%20will%20be%20no%20need%20for%20tanker%20water%20supply.%20Since%20you%E2%80%99ve%20not%20given%20piped%20water%20supply%20%5Bto%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20city%5D%2C%20then%20the%20solution%20lies%20in%20groundwater%20extraction.%20This%20means%20that%20when%20groundwater%20collapses%2C%20there%20is%20no%20alternative%20source%20of%20water%20supply%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20this%20point%20further%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20%5Bwater%5D%20problem%20in%20about%20three-fourths%20of%20the%20city.%20We%20got%201%2C470%20million%20litres%20of%20water%20%5Bper%20day%5D%20coming%20from%20the%20Cauvery%20%5Briver%5D%2C%20and%20there%20are%20about%201.1%20million%20%5Bpiped%20water%5D%20connections%20covering%2010%20people%20per%20connection.%20For%2011%20million%20residents%20of%20the%20city%2C%20this%20is%20not%20a%20problem.%20For%203%20to%203.5%20million%20people%20living%20in%20the%20outskirts%20dependent%20on%20groundwater%2C%20there%20are%20%5Bwater%20scarcity%5D%20problems%20in%20pockets.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%20the%20Bangalore%20Water%20Supply%20and%20Sewerage%20Board%20(BWSSB)%20issued%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fwater%2Fbengaluru-water-crisis-bwssb-announces-20-water-cut-to-bulk-consumers-identifies-areas-bearing-the-brunt-94973%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20detailed%20list%20%3C%2Fa%3Emarking%20out%20areas%20most%20severely%20impacted%20by%20water%20scarcity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20gathered%20from%20the%20Karnataka%20Groundwater%20Authority%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2Fbangalore%2Fbengaluru-east-taluk-worst-affected-in-depleting-groundwater-levels-this-summer%2Farticle68002688.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%2029%20March%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20data%20of%20groundwater%20levels%20for%20last%20December%20and%20this%20January%20and%20February%20shows%20that%20Bengaluru%20East%20taluk%2C%20which%20houses%20one%20of%20the%20major%20IT%20corridors%20of%20the%20city%2C%20where%20the%20water%20crisis%20is%20most%20severe%20and%20groundwater%20exploitation%20unbridled%2C%20has%20seen%20the%20most%20dip%20in%20groundwater%20levels%20this%20summer.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20why%20are%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20city%20struggling%20so%20much%20with%20water%20scarcity%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVishwanath%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20the%20perfect%20storm.%20What%20happened%20was%20that%20we%20were%20supposed%20to%20get%20water%20from%20the%20Cauvery%20Phase-5%20project%20(delivering%20775%20million%20litres%20a%20day)%2C%20and%20that%20should%20have%20been%20completed%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20ago.%20If%20this%20project%20had%20been%20completed%2C%20there%20would%20have%20been%20no%20crisis.%20With%20the%20completion%20of%20this%20project%2C%20millions%20of%20people%20in%20Bengaluru%20who%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20piped%20connection%20would%20have%20one%20with%20water%20flowing%20in%20it.%20But%20that%20project%20got%20delayed%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20in%20May-June%202024.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlso%2C%20some%20of%20the%20major%20city%20lakes%20have%20been%20drained%20and%20de-silted.%20That%20project%20should%20have%20been%20completed%20three%20years%20back%2C%20but%20this%20project%20has%20been%20going%20on%20for%20four%20to%20five%20years.%20If%20you%20desilt%20and%20drain%20lakes%20for%20these%20many%20years%2C%20their%20capacity%20to%20recharge%20aquifers%20is%20non-existent.%20That%E2%80%99s%20where%20all%20the%20borewells%20have%20dried%20up%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20parts%20of%20the%20city%2C%20however%2C%20the%20groundwater%20table%20is%20high%2C%20according%20to%20Vishwanath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20example%2C%20in%20Cubbon%20Park%2C%20the%20open%20recharge%20wells%20have%20sufficient%20water.%20Some%20of%20the%20lakes%2C%20which%20are%20full%20of%20water%2C%20are%20good%20for%20percolation.%20In%20these%20areas%2C%20the%20borewells%20are%20at%20a%20depth%20of%20150%20to%20300%20feet.%20Where%20there%20is%20no%20piped%20water%20supply%2C%20the%20groundwater%20table%20is%20very%20low.%20If%20the%20Cauvery%20Phase-5%20project%20is%20completed%2C%20the%20problem%20of%20water%20scarcity%20in%20the%20city%20will%20go%20away%20to%20a%20large%20extent.%20If%20the%20lakes%20are%20filled%20with%20rainwater%20or%20tertiary%20treated%20wastewater%2C%20then%20the%20aquifers%20will%20be%20recharged%20and%20the%20problem%20will%20become%20a%20lot%20less%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Vishwanath%20noted%20earlier%2C%20there%20are%20real%20problems%20that%20need%20to%20be%20solved%20to%20address%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F345780%2Fbengaluru-water-crisis-rain-reach-programme-hariharan-chandrashekhar-helps-children-in-bbmp-schools-conserve-water%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewater%20scarcity%20in%20the%20city%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20this%20article%2C%20we%20will%20highlight%20these%20problems%20and%20how%20we%20can%20solve%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-3-1712314897.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bengaluru%20Water%20Scarcity%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed%20soon%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-3-1712314897.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-3-1712314897-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-3-1712314897-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-3-1712314897-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-3-1712314897-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-346651%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ERepresentational%20Image%3A%20There%20are%20real%20problems%20that%20need%20to%20be%20solved%20to%20address%20water%20scarcity%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EReviving%20lakes%2C%20replenishing%20groundwater%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20it%E2%80%99s%20Chennai%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20or%20Hyderabad%2C%20before%20piped%20water%20connections%2C%20motorised%20pumps%20or%20electricity%20could%20come%20into%20play%2C%20residents%20were%20dependent%20on%20surface%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20as%20a%20result%20of%20rampant%20urbanisation%20in%20the%20city%2C%20lakes%20have%20become%20nothing%20but%20recreational%20and%20aesthetically%20appealing%20water-holding%20structures%20where%20the%20hydrology%20or%20science%20behind%20that%20water%20body%20is%20often%20forgotten.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20it%20also%20happens%20that%20throughout%20the%20year%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F172511%2Fbengaluru-lake-clean-hero-environment-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBengaluru%E2%80%99s%20lakes%3C%2Fa%3E%20hold%20sewage%2C%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20space%20for%20freshwater%20anymore.%20So%2C%20when%20rainfall%20happens%2C%20these%20lakes%20are%20filled%20with%20sewage%20to%20the%20brim%20and%20are%20not%20able%20to%20absorb%20that%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-4-1712315003.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bengaluru's%20water%20scarcity%20is%20due%20to%20rampant%20urbanisation%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-4-1712315003.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-4-1712315003-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-4-1712315003-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-4-1712315003-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBengaluru-Water-4-1712315003-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-346652%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ERampant%20urbanisation%20has%20destroyed%20water%20bodies%20in%20the%20city%3A%20Photo%20of%20Bagmane%20Tech%20Park%20taken%20in%20April%202013%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20this%20impacts%20the%20lake%20system%2C%20and%20thereby%20the%20groundwater.%20We%20are%20one%20of%20the%20most%20intense%20borewelling%20communities%20in%20the%20world.%20Nowhere%20else%20will%20you%20see%20so%20many%20borewells%20being%20dug%20everywhere%2C%20which%20technically%20depletes%20all%20the%20groundwater%20reserves%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Arun%20Krishnamurthy%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F104777%2Ftamil-nadu-drought-nagapattinam%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnvironmentalist%20Foundation%20of%20India%20(EFI)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20revives%20water%20bodies.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20groundwater%20reserves%20depleted%20and%20lakes%20holding%20sewage%2C%20which%20also%20means%20there%20is%20no%20space%20for%20freshwater%20from%20the%20monsoon%20rains%20to%20flow%20into%20%E2%80%94%20all%20these%20factors%20put%20together%20are%20causing%20this%20kind%20of%20drought.%20Bengaluru%20isn%E2%80%99t%20the%20first%20though%20given%20that%20Chennai%20went%20through%20something%20similar%20in%202018-19.%20Any%20urban%20pocket%20in%20India%20is%20bound%20to%20be%20affected%20by%20such%20a%20scenario%20given%20that%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20clear%20understanding%20of%20surface%20water%20bodies%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20how%20do%20you%20go%20about%20revving%20these%20water%20bodies%20and%20improving%20the%20groundwater%20level%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArun%20speaks%20of%20Devanahalli%20Kere%2C%20the%20first%20lake%20EFI%20took%20up%20in%20Bengaluru%20for%20revival%20in%202022.%20As%20an%20organisation%2C%20they%20have%20largely%20focussed%20on%20suburban%20Bengaluru%20rather%20than%20the%20main%20city%20area.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20suburban%20lakes%20were%20heading%20on%20the%20current%20path%20of%20the%20city%20lakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20data-origheight%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20data-epautoplay%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20data-facadesrc%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fr4iFfE90g_o%3Fenablejsapi%3D1%26amp%3Bautoplay%3D0%26amp%3Bcc_load_policy%3D0%26amp%3Bcc_lang_pref%3D%26amp%3Biv_load_policy%3D3%26amp%3Bloop%3D0%26amp%3Bmodestbranding%3D0%26amp%3Brel%3D0%26amp%3Bfs%3D1%26amp%3Bplaysinline%3D1%26amp%3Bautohide%3D2%26amp%3Btheme%3Ddark%26amp%3Bcolor%3Dred%26amp%3Bcontrols%3D1%26amp%3B%5C%22%20data-origwidth%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20data-spai-excluded%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ytimg.com%2Fvi%2Fr4iFfE90g_o%2Fmaxresdefault.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22YouTube%20player%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20prevent%20any%20kind%20of%20contamination%20or%20encroachment%2C%20we%20have%20taken%20up%20water%20bodies%20in%20Ramanagara%2C%20Tumkur%2C%20and%20Bengaluru%20(Rural)%20districts%2C%20and%20the%20closest%20such%20lake%20to%20the%20main%20city%20is%20the%20Devanahalli%20Lake.%20Within%20Karahalli%2C%20which%20is%20next%20to%20Devanahalli%2C%20we%20have%20revived%20at%20least%20five%20water%20bodies.%20What%20we%20have%20achieved%20is%20deepening%20these%20water%20bodies%20to%20increase%20storage%20capacity%2C%20regulating%20their%20inlet%20and%20outlet%20channels%20so%20that%20there%20is%20a%20free%20flow%20of%20water%2C%20and%20we%20have%20also%20ensured%20recharge%20wells%20have%20been%20created%20in%20all%20these%20systems%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Arun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBuilding%20these%20recharge%20wells%20is%20all%20about%20ensuring%20there%20is%20enough%20groundwater%20percolation.%20Creating%20a%20water%20holding%20structure%20based%20on%20the%20soil%20structure%2C%20understanding%20its%20utilisation%20value%20to%20the%20region%2C%20and%20creating%20percolation%20trenches%20and%20recharge%20wells%20have%20all%20been%20our%20key%20focus%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20in%20Devanahalli%2C%20Karahalli%2C%20the%20Baddihalli%20Lake%20in%20Tumkur%20city%2C%20or%20the%20Hulikunte%20lake.%20EFI%20has%20restored%20all%20these%20water%20bodies%20with%20this%20larger%20point%20in%20mind%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20impact%20of%20all%20these%20initiatives%20on%20the%20communities%20who%20live%20near%20these%20lakes%20has%20been%20visible.%20%E2%80%9CTheir%20borewells%20are%20not%20as%20dry%20as%20what%20we%20hear%20from%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20city.%20These%20lakes%2C%20which%20were%20often%20used%20as%20dumping%20sites%2C%20are%20now%20no%20longer%20perceived%20as%20such.%20People%20want%20to%20protect%20them.%20When%20droughts%20occur%2C%20people%20realise%20and%20understand%20the%20significance%20of%20these%20lakes%20