res%3C%2Fa%3E%20served%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20founder%20Ganesh%20Chandra%20Mullick%20came%20to%20Kolkata%20from%20Konnagar%20in%201880.%20He%20worked%20for%20three%20years%20as%20a%20sweet%20%3Cem%3Ekarigar%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20North%20Kolkata%20shop%20before%20setting%20up%20Balaram%20Mullick%20%26amp%3B%20Radharaman%20Mullick%20in%201883%20in%20Bhowanipore%20(South%20Kolkata)%20on%20a%20450%20sq%20ft%20land.%20The%20eatery%20is%20now%20famous%20for%20its%20%3Cem%3Ekorapak%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20Bengali%20sweet%20made%20with%20cottage%20cheese)%20and%20%3Cem%3Enolen%20gur%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20special%20jaggery%20found%20in%20Bengal).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Emergency%2C%20when%20milk%20was%20banned%2C%20the%20women%20of%20the%20family%20stepped%20up%20to%20create%20sweets%20out%20of%20cashews%20and%20pulses%20to%20keep%20the%20business%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Chittaranjan%20Mistanna%20Bhandar%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20major%20draw%20here%20is%20the%20spongy%2C%20sweet%2C%20dribbling%20in%20sugar%20syrup%20%3Cem%3Erosogolla.%20%3C%2Fem%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20iconic%20Chittaranjan%20Mistanna%20Bhandar%20is%20one%20of%20the%2071%20certified%20sweet%20shops%20in%20the%20city%20to%20sell%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F225831%2Fnortheast-india-food-gi-tag-chak-hao-rice-boka-saul-queen-pineapple-superfood-ang136%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20GI%20product%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20%3Cem%3Erosogollas%3C%2Fem%3E%20at%20this%20115-year-old%20eatery%20are%20delightful%20%E2%80%94%20earning%20the%20sweet%20outlet%20the%20name%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ERosogolla%20Wala%20of%20Kolkata%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20their%20%3Cem%3Emadhuporko%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20sweet%20made%20from%20curd%2C%20ghee%20and%20honey)%20is%20equally%20amazing.%20And%20a%20fan%20of%20it%20is%20none%20other%20than%20Indian%20chef%20Saransh%20Goila.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FxLiAgsgoMuM%3Fsi%3DZHrL2_-z6II9NI70%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E6.%20Girish%20Chandra%20Dey%20And%20Nakur%20Chandra%20Nandy%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20love%20Calcutta.%20The%20food%20is%20just%20brilliant.%20Every%20time%20I%20go%2C%20I%20must%20have%20sweets%20from%20Nakur%20(Girish%20Chandra%20Dey%20%26amp%3B%20Nakur%20Chandra%20Nandy)%2C%20especially%20the%20%3Cem%3Ejolbhora%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Emanohara%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20celebrity%20chef%20Ranveer%20Brar%20shared%20in%20an%20article%20with%3Cem%3E%20Telegraph%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20eatery%20is%20a%20renowned%20one%20in%20Kolkata%20and%20one%20of%20the%20most%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F235277%2Findian-traditional-food-dessert-sweets-beautiful-art-festive-cuisine-ornamental-foods-visual-treat-india-ana79%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegendary%20sweet%20places%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20their%20website%20states%2C%20Nakur%20Chandra%20Nandy%20was%20the%20son-in-law%20of%20the%20renowned%20confectioner%20of%20Shimla%2C%20Girish%20Chandra%20Dey.%20The%20venture%20is%20a%20joint%20initiative%20by%20the%20duo%20and%20their%20%3Cem%3Esandesh%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20found%20love%20in%20many%20personalities%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20Abhishek%20Bachchan%2C%20Aishwarya%20Rai%2C%20West%20Bengal%20Chief%20Minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee%2C%20and%20Satyajit%20Ray%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F5_MAb7EjaEQ%3Fsi%3DwbjerIdFO1iVudi5%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E7.%20Bhim%20Chandra%20Nag%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20640px)%20100vw%2C%20640px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FFQjcCqzaMAAeXxF-1710247668.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ledikeni%20is%20a%20popular%20Bengali%20sweet%20that%20is%20named%20after%20Lady%20Canning%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FFQjcCqzaMAAeXxF-1710247668.jpg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FFQjcCqzaMAAeXxF-1710247668-300x188.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FFQjcCqzaMAAeXxF-1710247668-500x313.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FFQjcCqzaMAAeXxF-1710247668-150x94.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-344632%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELedikeni%20is%20a%20popular%20Bengali%20sweet%20that%20is%20named%20after%20Lady%20Canning%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Twitter%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fvernaculartube%2Fstatus%2F1515703329284042754%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAjatshatru%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECredited%20with%20creating%20the%20%3Cem%3Eledikeni%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20popular%20Bengali%20sweet%2C%20this%20sweet%20shop%2C%20over%20two%20centuries%20old%2C%20has%20watched%20the%20city%20evolve%20into%20its%20present%20form.%20At%20the%20turn%20of%20the%2019th%20century%2C%20as%20reform%20and%20renaissance%20were%20rife%20in%20Bengal%2C%20sweet%20shops%20began%20mushrooming%20across%20the%20city.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20Paran%20Chandra%20Nag%2C%20too%2C%20decided%20to%20channel%20his%20skills%20into%20%3Cem%3Emithai%3C%2Fem%3E%20making%