%20using%20this%20method%20to%20grow%20fodder%20for%20his%20livestock.%20What%E2%80%99s%20unique%20about%20it%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20grows%20it%20in%20his%20cupboard!%20He%20uses%20the%20soilless%20hydroponic%20method%20to%20grow%20maize%20fodder.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20in%202018%2C%20he%20received%20the%20Haldhar%20Organic%20farmer%20award%20from%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Agricultural%20Research%20along%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98Innovative%20farmer%20award%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20Central%20government%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20did%20a%20farmer%20practising%20traditional%20farming%20in%20a%20village%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20move%20to%20organic%20methods%20and%20find%20success%20in%20them%3F%20Here%E2%80%99s%20his%20story.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EAn%20attempt%20to%20save%20soil%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201600px)%20100vw%2C%201600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan-min-1712145955.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Saravanan%20has%20been%20practicing%20organic%20farming%20since%202008%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan-min-1712145955.jpeg%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan-min-1712145955-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan-min-1712145955-500x281.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan-min-1712145955-768x432.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan-min-1712145955-1536x864.jpeg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan-min-1712145955-150x84.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-346392%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESaravanan%20has%20been%20practicing%20organic%20farming%20since%202008%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EP%20Saravanan%20has%20been%20farming%20for%20over%2040%20years%20now%20in%20Ariyagoundampatti%20village%2C%20Namakkal%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20While%20his%20grandparents%20practised%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F304986%2Fkerala-aluva-seed-farm-first-in-india-to-become-carbon-neutral%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorganic%20methods%20of%20farming%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20his%20father%20introduced%20chemicals%20and%20pesticides%2C%20which%20Saravanan%20continued%20till%202006%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20introduced%20the%20micro-irrigation%20scheme%20in%202005-06%2C%20under%20which%20subsidies%20were%20provided%20for%20drip%20and%20sprinkler%20irrigation.%20Saravanan%2C%20an%20early%20adopter%20of%20many%20such%20new%3Cbr%3Eschemes%2C%20decided%20to%20give%20drip%20irrigation%20a%20try.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20to%20face%20water%20scarcity%2C%20which%20made%20irrigation%20very%20difficult.%20Drip%20irrigation%20saves%20water%20and%20irrigates%20thrice%20the%20amount%20of%20land%20using%20the%20same%20water%20used%20by%20traditional%20methods%2C%E2%80%9D%20Saravanan%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202007%2C%20the%20farmer%20has%20moved%20to%20drip%20irrigation%20on%20his%206%20acre%20and%2036%20cents%20(1%20acre%20is%20100%20cents)%20land%20on%20which%20he%20cultivates%20turmeric%2C%20groundnuts%2C%20and%20vegetables.%20He%20also%20practises%20integrated%20farming%2C%20a%20sustainable%20agricultural%20system%20where%20crops%2C%20livestock%2C%20aquaculture%2C%20poultry%20are%20managed%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20these%20crops%2C%20he%20also%20manages%20livestock%